The Equality and Human Rights Commission releases a 700-page report condemning Britain as a land where discrimination and disadvantage are rife. (The Observer)British judge Heather Hallett opens the inquests into the 7 July 2005 London bombings. (Reuters UK)The trial of Ahmed Ghailani, the first Guantanamo Bay prisoner to face a criminal trial in the United States, begins in New York City. (Reuters)